President Donald Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of South Dakota due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is now available for emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, for all areas in South Dakota impacted by COVID-19. Lee K. dePalo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and deemed necessary after further assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.